The paper deals with the interpretation of deep neural networks for object classification, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the comparison of different architectures, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of semantic meaning in the visual summaries suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of image patterns, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
